1
00:00:21,855 --> 00:00:27,528
[giggle] Oh, wow, you were
right! The little one's so
cuuute!

2
00:00:27,594 --> 00:00:29,029
<i>(Kyusuk)</i>
<i>Told y!</i>

3
00:00:29,029 --> 00:00:30,697
When did you find them?

4
00:00:30,764 --> 00:00:32,699
They've been here
for about a week.

5
00:00:32,699 --> 00:00:35,536
It's funny, they show up every
winter around this time.

6
00:00:35,536 --> 00:00:36,703
Ah...

7
00:00:36,803 --> 00:00:40,040
I heard that swans migrate all
the way from Siberia...

8
00:00:40,106 --> 00:00:41,041
<i>(Hiroki)</i>
<i>Outta the way!!!</i>

9
00:00:41,041 --> 00:00:42,208
(All)
Huh?!

10
00:00:42,876 --> 00:00:44,711
<i>(Kyusuke)</i>
<i>Hey, whoa, whoa, whoa‐‐!!</i>

11
00:00:44,778 --> 00:00:45,879
Look out!

12
00:00:46,212 --> 00:00:48,782
<i>(Kyusuke)</i>
<i>Watch it, watch it!!</i>

13
00:00:49,816 --> 00:00:53,186
Ahhh...!

14
00:00:53,219 --> 00:00:55,722
[gasps]

15
00:00:56,723 --> 00:00:58,324
<i>(Chibi‐Usa)</i>
<i>He's flying!</i>

16
00:01:01,401 --> 00:01:03,870
<i>(Kyusuke)</i>
<i>No, he's falling!</i>

17
00:01:03,904 --> 00:01:06,306
[screaming]

18
00:01:06,339 --> 00:01:07,574
[splash]

19
00:01:08,241 --> 00:01:10,476
Hey! You all
right down there?

20
00:01:10,511 --> 00:01:13,246
[groan]

21
00:01:13,313 --> 00:01:13,914
Hey‐‐

22
00:01:13,914 --> 00:01:15,248
Isn't that...?

23
00:01:15,315 --> 00:01:17,150
Yeah, from our school!

24
00:01:17,350 --> 00:01:20,253
<i>(Kyusuke)</i>
<i>Hiroki?... Hiroki,</i>
<i>is that you?!</i>

25
00:01:21,922 --> 00:01:31,998
♪

26
00:01:31,998 --> 00:01:52,018
♪

27
00:01:52,018 --> 00:02:12,045
♪

28
00:02:12,045 --> 00:02:32,132
♪

29
00:02:32,132 --> 00:02:51,117
♪

30
00:02:59,526 --> 00:03:03,136
<i>(Usagi)</i>
<i>Pegasus Disappears:</i>
<i>Wavering Friendship</i>

31
00:03:05,038 --> 00:03:06,873
(Chibi‐Usa)
A homebuilt aircraft?

32
00:03:06,940 --> 00:03:11,512
Mhm. Yeah, that's my dream. To
fly in my own aircraft.

33
00:03:11,545 --> 00:03:13,346
One that I built myself.

34
00:03:13,379 --> 00:03:14,681
Aircraft?

35
00:03:14,715 --> 00:03:17,050
What, you mean
that old bike?

36
00:03:17,117 --> 00:03:20,053
It's a lot more than just a
bike, it's the “St. Louis. ”

37
00:03:20,120 --> 00:03:21,522
Oh, come on!

38
00:03:21,555 --> 00:03:26,059
If bikes could fly,
the sky would be full
of flying bikes.

39
00:03:26,126 --> 00:03:28,729
Well, just wait, my
St. Louis will fly!

40
00:03:28,795 --> 00:03:33,233
I designed and built every part
of it by myself, so I just know
it'll fly.

41
00:03:33,299 --> 00:03:36,069
Yeah? Well, it did a pretty
good job of crashing.

42
00:03:36,136 --> 00:03:37,504
You got that part down.

43
00:03:37,804 --> 00:03:41,575
Argh! What was that for?

44
00:03:41,575 --> 00:03:43,076
You are such an idiot!

45
00:03:43,076 --> 00:03:45,411
Have some respect for
this boy's dream!

46
00:03:45,411 --> 00:03:47,413
Yeah, but that hurt.

47
00:03:47,413 --> 00:03:49,382
Well, I think it's cool.

48
00:03:49,415 --> 00:03:50,717
That she hit me?!

49
00:03:50,751 --> 00:03:53,554
It's great to put so much
passion into something.

50
00:03:53,587 --> 00:03:55,388
I love people who do that!

51
00:03:55,421 --> 00:03:57,658
Aw, c'mon, really!?

52
00:03:57,691 --> 00:03:59,593
Hiroki, if I can
help at all‐‐

53
00:03:59,593 --> 00:04:01,602
No, this is my dream...

54
00:04:01,602 --> 00:04:05,906
Sorry, but this is something
I've gotta do with just the St.
Louis and me.

55
00:04:05,939 --> 00:04:08,108
Thanks for the jacket.

56
00:04:08,174 --> 00:04:09,610
But...

57
00:04:09,943 --> 00:04:11,277
Let him go.

58
00:04:15,882 --> 00:04:17,518
So rude, what gives?

59
00:04:17,551 --> 00:04:18,284
Oh well...

60
00:04:18,351 --> 00:04:20,286
[sigh]

61
00:04:23,289 --> 00:04:26,092
This boy Hiroki is
probably feeling lost...

62
00:04:26,126 --> 00:04:27,260
Lost?

63
00:04:27,293 --> 00:04:30,363
He's frustrated he can't
get his aircraft to fly.

64
00:04:30,396 --> 00:04:34,801
And the more frustrated he
gets, the more he wants to
do it all himself.

65
00:04:34,868 --> 00:04:39,138
What he really needs are friends
to share his dream with.

66
00:04:39,205 --> 00:04:43,109
I wish Hiroki would
let us be his friends.

67
00:04:43,143 --> 00:04:46,146
I think I'll go see him again
tomorrow, to cheer him on.

68
00:04:46,146 --> 00:04:47,548
I'd like to see it, too.

69
00:04:47,581 --> 00:04:48,414
Huh?

70
00:04:48,448 --> 00:04:51,151
That moment when he
leaves the ground...

71
00:04:51,151 --> 00:04:56,657
I'm sorry, it's just
that well, You see...

72
00:04:56,657 --> 00:05:04,270
<i>I reside in the Dream World...</i>
<i>and here in this world... I am</i>
<i>unable to fly about freely...</i>

73
00:05:04,771 --> 00:05:08,341
<i>[gasp]</i>
<i>(Thinking)</i>
<i>The Dream World?</i>

74
00:05:08,408 --> 00:05:16,817
<i>Where is this Dream World?...</i>
<i>Where are you right now?</i>

75
00:05:16,850 --> 00:05:19,853
Pegasus?

76
00:05:25,025 --> 00:05:26,927
[sigh]

77
00:05:26,960 --> 00:05:28,862
All right, then!

78
00:05:28,862 --> 00:05:33,199
Why don't you come with me,
Pegasus, and we'll both watch
Hiroki fly!

79
00:05:33,199 --> 00:05:34,434
No, I‐‐

80
00:05:34,467 --> 00:05:37,037
Don't worry! I'll take
care of everything‐‐

81
00:05:37,103 --> 00:05:38,438
Argh!
Chibi‐Usa...

82
00:05:38,471 --> 00:05:41,542
What're you doing? Don't you
knock when entering a lady's
room?

83
00:05:41,542 --> 00:05:45,378
You were having a secret
lovey‐dovey phone call with
Mamo, weren't you?

84
00:05:45,378 --> 00:05:47,347
Why would I be doing that?

85
00:05:47,380 --> 00:05:50,283
Ah‐ha! Of course
you're gonna deny it!

86
00:05:50,316 --> 00:05:54,220
But then how come Mamo's line is
busy every time I try and call
him...

87
00:05:54,220 --> 00:05:57,558
...and then I hear a guy's voice
coming from your room‐‐

88
00:05:57,624 --> 00:06:00,727
Oh, Mamo, how could you betray
me? And with <i>her?</i>

89
00:06:00,727 --> 00:06:03,904
All right, come on,
admit it, Chibi‐Usa!

90
00:06:03,904 --> 00:06:07,641
Mamo's got an online seminar
tonight, that's why his line's
busy.

91
00:06:07,674 --> 00:06:08,742
That's tonight?

92
00:06:08,742 --> 00:06:11,578
You told me so yourself
just this afternoon.

93
00:06:11,578 --> 00:06:15,248
[laugh] That's right, I did!

94
00:06:15,248 --> 00:06:18,652
Good grief. Well, I'm gonna go
to bed now, so d'ya mind‐‐?

95
00:06:18,685 --> 00:06:20,754
Right, sorry. Goodnight!

96
00:06:21,421 --> 00:06:24,090
Good. Night.

97
00:06:25,491 --> 00:06:30,997
Don't worry, Pegasus. Our secret
is still a secret.

98
00:06:37,604 --> 00:06:43,443
So, Zirconia... you still
haven't managed to find
Pegasus, I see.

99
00:06:43,443 --> 00:06:49,282
Sadly, those girls have proven
incapable of overcoming certain
obstacles.

100
00:06:49,349 --> 00:06:51,284
The Sailor Guardians.

101
00:06:51,284 --> 00:06:57,290
Don't keep repeating the same
mistakes or I will be most
displeased. Is that clear?

102
00:06:57,357 --> 00:06:59,192
My queen.

103
00:06:59,860 --> 00:07:05,038
<i>This is our new target, huh?</i>

104
00:07:05,071 --> 00:07:08,208
Doesn't really do it
for me. Not my type.

105
00:07:08,241 --> 00:07:11,645
Well, fine, then. No
one's forcing you to go.

106
00:07:11,712 --> 00:07:14,280
Hey, I wasn't saying
I wouldn't go!

107
00:07:14,314 --> 00:07:15,649
Sounded that way to me.

108
00:07:15,649 --> 00:07:17,784
Hey, hey, hey!

109
00:07:17,818 --> 00:07:18,719
What?

110
00:07:18,752 --> 00:07:21,788
Maybe Palla‐Palla ought to go.

111
00:07:21,822 --> 00:07:22,989
You too, huh?

112
00:07:22,989 --> 00:07:25,325
Then why don't we play
rock‐paper‐scissors for it?

113
00:07:25,391 --> 00:07:28,562
Don't bother. I've already got
dibs on this one, ladies.

114
00:07:28,595 --> 00:07:30,330
What're you talking
about? Since when?

115
00:07:30,396 --> 00:07:31,665
Look!

116
00:07:31,732 --> 00:07:33,066
Huh!?

117
00:07:33,099 --> 00:07:35,168
<i>(Cere‐Cere)</i>
<i>Wait, you're saying just</i>
<i>because you drew a‐‐?</i>

118
00:07:35,168 --> 00:07:38,505
Yep. This one's mine. So
you girls enjoy your bath.

119
00:07:38,505 --> 00:07:41,341
Huh. Wish I'd thought a' that.

120
00:07:41,341 --> 00:07:43,176
[sigh]

121
00:07:49,249 --> 00:07:52,919
There, Pegasus, that's
Hiroki's flying machine.

122
00:07:52,953 --> 00:07:54,588
Can you see it all right?

123
00:07:54,621 --> 00:07:56,322
Yes. That's amazing.

124
00:07:56,356 --> 00:07:58,659
<i>...He really</i>
<i>built it by himself?</i>

125
00:07:58,692 --> 00:08:04,538
Yeah. And you should have seen
it yesterday, it was all mangled
up and he's already put it back
together.

126
00:08:04,605 --> 00:08:05,872
That's a lot of work.

127
00:08:05,939 --> 00:08:08,709
Chibi‐Usa, why are you
talking to your lunchbox?

128
00:08:08,709 --> 00:08:10,176
How'd you know where I was?

129
00:08:10,210 --> 00:08:14,380
You really shouldn't
underestimate my extensive
surveillance network.

130
00:08:14,380 --> 00:08:15,649
Hey!

131
00:08:15,682 --> 00:08:18,685
Sorry to butt in, but we wanted
to see the St. Louis, too.

132
00:08:18,719 --> 00:08:21,555
WoW! So that's really a
human‐powered aircraft?

133
00:08:21,555 --> 00:08:23,289
Aah, it's just a bike.

134
00:08:23,323 --> 00:08:24,858
It's an aircraft!!

135
00:08:24,891 --> 00:08:26,793
Whoa, he's got good ears.

136
00:08:26,827 --> 00:08:29,796
Human flight, that's an
ambitious dream.

137
00:08:29,830 --> 00:08:30,797
I know!

138
00:08:30,831 --> 00:08:32,999
Look! He's getting
ready to go!

139
00:08:38,238 --> 00:08:40,741
[panting]

140
00:08:52,653 --> 00:08:53,386
Go!

141
00:08:53,419 --> 00:08:55,188
Keep going! You got this!

142
00:08:56,657 --> 00:08:59,225
[grunt]

143
00:08:59,259 --> 00:09:01,267
Come on, Hiroki!

144
00:09:06,272 --> 00:09:08,008
He did it!

145
00:09:10,043 --> 00:09:12,613
[rattling]

146
00:09:13,847 --> 00:09:14,447
[gasps]

147
00:09:14,447 --> 00:09:15,281
[screaming]

148
00:09:15,281 --> 00:09:17,350
Hiroki!

149
00:09:21,454 --> 00:09:24,124
You sure you're all
right, Hiroki?

150
00:09:24,190 --> 00:09:27,460
Why don't it fly?

151
00:09:27,528 --> 00:09:28,962
Well, let's see!

152
00:09:28,962 --> 00:09:29,796
Here you go, take a look.

153
00:09:29,863 --> 00:09:30,964
Hey, wait‐‐

154
00:09:30,964 --> 00:09:33,934
Heh! Don't you worry, just
leave it to my friend Ami!

155
00:09:33,967 --> 00:09:37,470
Wow! This is really remarkable
work you've done.

156
00:09:37,538 --> 00:09:42,876
My only suggestion would be to
streamline the aerodynamics and
maybe reinforce the framework of
the wings a bit.

157
00:09:42,909 --> 00:09:45,478
Plus, a little more
muscle‐power wouldn't hurt.

158
00:09:45,546 --> 00:09:46,980
Hm, that's true.

159
00:09:47,047 --> 00:09:49,650
<i>You're definitely on the</i>
<i>skinny side, Hiroki.</i>

160
00:09:49,650 --> 00:09:53,119
Make it a two‐seater!
That could help!

161
00:09:53,153 --> 00:09:55,388
Great idea! I
could be co‐pilot!

162
00:09:55,421 --> 00:09:57,991
That would be way
too much weight.

163
00:09:58,058 --> 00:09:59,660
That was harsh, Rei.

164
00:09:59,726 --> 00:10:01,267
I'd ride with you!

165
00:10:01,334 --> 00:10:02,836
Wow, you're so brave!

166
00:10:02,869 --> 00:10:03,670
Stop it.

167
00:10:03,704 --> 00:10:05,205
‐Huh?
‐Huh?

168
00:10:05,238 --> 00:10:08,074
Stop it! This is my dream! Why
can't you all just leave me
alone?

169
00:10:08,108 --> 00:10:11,778
Hey, that attitude of yours is
prob'ly the reason you keep on
crashing!

170
00:10:11,778 --> 00:10:16,950
Stop being stubborn. Flying's
one of the oldest dreams shared
by all of humanity.

171
00:10:17,017 --> 00:10:22,188
After all, the Wright brothers
would have never even gotten off
the ground if they hadn't worked
together.

172
00:10:22,222 --> 00:10:26,292
Yeah, okay, that was a little
cheesy, but you get my point.
We wanna help.

173
00:10:26,359 --> 00:10:28,461
Thanks, Kyusuke,
you're right

174
00:10:28,461 --> 00:10:31,431
Calm down. Don't
get all mushy...

175
00:10:31,464 --> 00:10:36,202
Here. Shake on it.

176
00:10:36,236 --> 00:10:39,973
That's sweet, the beginning
of a new friendship.

177
00:10:40,040 --> 00:10:42,042
Friendship..?

178
00:10:43,309 --> 00:10:46,713
So, if we move this...

179
00:10:46,747 --> 00:10:49,482
It's wonderful to have a friend
you can share everything with.

180
00:10:49,550 --> 00:10:52,753
<i>(Thinking)</i>
<i>A friend to share</i>
<i>everything with...</i>

181
00:10:55,055 --> 00:10:58,725
Pegasus, are we friends?
Real friends?

182
00:10:58,759 --> 00:11:00,466
Why do you ask?

183
00:11:00,500 --> 00:11:02,736
Don't you like me?

184
00:11:02,769 --> 00:11:04,838
Course I do, I like you a lot.

185
00:11:04,905 --> 00:11:07,674
That's why I've always been
honest and told you everything.

186
00:11:07,674 --> 00:11:09,342
But what about you?

187
00:11:09,342 --> 00:11:14,515
I don't really know much about
you, Pegasus... Because you
won't tell me anything.

188
00:11:14,581 --> 00:11:19,853
I still can't tell you
even now. I'm sorry.

189
00:11:19,920 --> 00:11:20,921
But why?

190
00:11:20,954 --> 00:11:24,825
I'm right here in front of
you. Isn't that enough?

191
00:11:24,858 --> 00:11:27,528
Friends tell each other
everything.

192
00:11:27,594 --> 00:11:31,097
If you can't, then maybe you
don't really think of me as
your friend.

193
00:11:31,131 --> 00:11:38,038
If you can't put your trust in
me... then I can't remain by
your side any longer.

194
00:11:38,104 --> 00:11:40,674
[gasp] No, wait!

195
00:11:40,707 --> 00:11:45,111
Please... you have
to trust me.

196
00:11:46,479 --> 00:11:51,284
[gasp] No, don't go!
Pegasus, please come back!

197
00:12:02,402 --> 00:12:07,007
<i>♪ Sailor Moon</i>

198
00:12:14,414 --> 00:12:20,821
<i>♪ Sailor Moon</i>

199
00:12:26,593 --> 00:12:31,364
<i>(Thinking)</i>
<i>Pegasus... Why won't you answer</i>
<i>any of my questions?</i>

200
00:12:33,199 --> 00:12:36,102
<i>Why did you have to go away?</i>

201
00:12:36,102 --> 00:12:40,406
<i>Does this mean we're not</i>
<i>friends after all?...</i>

202
00:12:40,440 --> 00:12:42,509
<i>I thought we</i>
<i>understood each other...</i>

203
00:12:42,543 --> 00:12:44,778
<i>(Mamor)</i>
<i>Chibi‐Us?</i>

204
00:12:44,778 --> 00:12:47,180
What are you doing out
here at this hour?

205
00:12:47,213 --> 00:12:48,615
Mamo...

206
00:12:48,615 --> 00:12:51,117
How 'bout you let me
take you home now.

207
00:12:51,117 --> 00:12:52,452
Mm.

208
00:12:55,889 --> 00:12:59,259
Mamo? Do you and Usagi
ever get into arguments?

209
00:12:59,292 --> 00:13:00,360
Huh?

210
00:13:00,393 --> 00:13:02,468
Do you always tell each
other everything?

211
00:13:02,468 --> 00:13:03,804
Yeah, pretty much!

212
00:13:03,870 --> 00:13:06,306
We don't have many secrets after
all we've been through,

213
00:13:06,306 --> 00:13:08,942
and besides, Usako, can't
keep a secret anyway.

214
00:13:08,975 --> 00:13:14,447
That's true. And after all, you
and Usagi are more than just
friends, aren't you?

215
00:13:14,480 --> 00:13:15,649
What's wrong?

216
00:13:15,649 --> 00:13:17,117
<i>(Usagi)</i>
<i>Chibi‐Usa!</i>

217
00:13:17,150 --> 00:13:17,718
oh...

218
00:13:17,751 --> 00:13:19,052
...Usagi!

219
00:13:19,085 --> 00:13:22,155
I've finally found you. C'mon,
let's go home, it's late.

220
00:13:22,222 --> 00:13:24,057
No!

221
00:13:24,090 --> 00:13:25,559
What's wrong?

222
00:13:25,592 --> 00:13:29,329
Stop! You wouldn't understand
anyway, so just leave me alone!

223
00:13:29,329 --> 00:13:32,966
You're always doing this!
Peeking in my room, and
spying on me..!

224
00:13:32,999 --> 00:13:35,836
I'm sorry, but you seemed
upset about something.

225
00:13:35,836 --> 00:13:38,004
I was only trying to help you.

226
00:13:38,071 --> 00:13:40,507
Well, don't. It's none
of your business!

227
00:13:40,507 --> 00:13:42,976
Maybe I have things I
don't want to tell you‐‐!

228
00:13:43,009 --> 00:13:44,344
[gasp]

229
00:13:44,344 --> 00:13:46,980
I still can't tell
you. I'm sorry.

230
00:13:47,013 --> 00:13:51,251
<i>(Thinking)</i>
<i>Just like Pegasus has</i>
<i>things he can't tell me...</i>

231
00:13:55,188 --> 00:13:58,592
Okay, I'll go on ahead.
I'll see you at home.

232
00:13:58,625 --> 00:14:00,026
[gasp]

233
00:14:10,977 --> 00:14:13,547
Okay, today's the day,
Chibi‐Usa!

234
00:14:13,547 --> 00:14:15,649
C'mon take a look!

235
00:14:16,149 --> 00:14:18,685
<i>Kyusuke helped me modify</i>
<i>a few things.</i>

236
00:14:18,719 --> 00:14:24,625
Ami had some good advice, too,
and it made me realize... it's
great to have friends.

237
00:14:24,658 --> 00:14:26,560
